		<h2> Ways To Save Water</h2>
			<p>
				<ul>
					 <li>Place a bucket under the faucet while the water either gets warmer or colder.  Keep the water in the bucket and you can use it to water your plants later on.
            		 <li>While you are brushing your teeth and washing your hands, make sure to turn the water off unless necessary.
            		 <li>Take shorter showers.
            		 <li>Use your leftover pasta cooking water to water your plants(just make sure that it is completely cooled down!!)
            		 <li>If you're hand washing your dishes, fill the sink with water and use that to scrub them instead of letting the water run.
            		 <li>Using less electricity will also help save water.
            		 <li>An average shower only takes 8.2 minutes which means you only use 16 gallons of water every time you shower.
            		 <li>One way to help keep the water clean, is by using gravels, paver stones, wood, or porous materials whenever possible in your driveway.
            		 <li> Do not throw away nondegradable products dow the toilet(only toilet paper) They can wind up being on our beach shores!
            		 <li> Don't let paint, used oil, chemical cleaners or other questionable household products go down the drain. They may contain toxic ingredients.

            	</ul>
			</p>
			<img src = "http://www.herndon-group.com/sites/default/files/styles/complete_small/public/news/fix_a_leak-infographic-household_leaks_waste.jpg">

		<h2> Effects From Around The World</h2>
			<p>
				<ul>
					<li>70% of industrial waste is dumped into waters where it then becomes polluted.
					<li> Many sea creatures such as fish, blue crabs, and oysters die from lack of oxygen due to the water pollution.
					<li> Water pollution can even have an effect on farms and various soils.
					<li> More than 1 billion people lack access to clean water and 2.4 billion people don't have proper sanitation, putting them at risk of deadly diseases.
					<li> One of the many ways that our oceans become polluted is from containers that fall off of ships during storms. Those containers usually hold toxic waste.
					<li>Trash that washes off of city streets into rivers, then end up in the ocean.
					<li> Pollution makes life difficult for people and animals all around the world.
					<li>650 million people lack access to clean water.
					<li>315 thousand <strong>CHILDREN</strong> pass away due to dieseases because they don't have clean water.
					<li>Afghanistan, Ethiopia, Cambodia, India, and Haiti are just a few
					of the places that don't have access to water, let alone clean water.
				</ul>
			</p>

